  "text": "Proof. The method from [CITATION_1] starts with choosing a model, which consists of a set M, and for each function symbol f in the original signature with arity n a mapping f M : M n → M, such that for every rewrite rule, and for all possible values for its variables in the model, the left-hand side and the right-hand side are equal in the model. Here we choose the model to be the positive natural numbers. Each process p is interpreted by its norm |p|, being the least number of steps in which it can terminate. This norm can be defined inductively as follows:",
